+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("Overall conclusion: the strongest patterns were clinically coherent treatment-biomarker relationships: pembrolizumab with MSI-high disease, encorafenib with BRAF V600E, trastuzumab/tucatinib with HER2 amplification, and reduced cetuximab benefit in RAS-mutant or right-sided disease. Baseline inflammatory, nutritional, and metastatic-burden variables also carried independent prognostic information for progression-free survival. Several safety/comorbidity interaction ideas were tested but not statistically supported in this cohort.");
