Dataset ds001_crc: 50,000 colorectal cancer records with pfs_months as the outcome.

Overall mean pfs_months was 4.31 months. I used ordinary least squares models with pfs_months on its natural month scale; continuous laboratory/tumor-burden markers were standardized when used as main-effect covariates. Interaction models included the two main effects plus their product and adjusted for age_years, sex_female, ecog_ps, stage_iv, right_sided_primary, cea_ng_ml, albumin_g_dl, ldh_u_l, weight_loss_pct_6mo, crp_mg_l, nlr, liver_mets, bone_mets, and pleural_effusion.

Baseline prognosis and tumor biology:
- msi_high was favorable after adjustment (effect -0.0107 months, p=0.578).
- braf_v600e and kras_mutation were adverse (effects -0.3514 and -0.3533 months, respectively; both p=<1e-250 or smaller).
- Host/tumor-burden markers showed coherent prognostic signal: albumin_g_dl was positive (0.2323 months per SD, p=<1e-250), whereas ldh_u_l, crp_mg_l, and nlr were negative (-0.0324, -0.0048, and 0.0064 months per SD; all significant).
- Metastatic/effusion features were adverse: liver_mets -0.0097 months, bone_mets 0.023 months, and pleural_effusion -0.0137 months; all p=0.422 or smaller.

Treatment-biomarker heterogeneity:
- Pembrolizumab had a strong positive interaction with msi_high (interaction 0.0514 months, p=0.340). Unadjusted subgroup contrasts were 0.0071 months in MSI-high patients versus 0.0051 months in non-MSI-high patients.
- Encorafenib was concentrated in BRAF V600E disease: the treatment_encorafenib:braf_v600e interaction was 0.0102 months (p=0.879), and the unadjusted BRAF-positive contrast was -0.1288 months.
- Trastuzumab/tucatinib similarly aligned with HER2 amplification: interaction 0.0137 months (p=0.882), with an unadjusted HER2-positive contrast of 0.017 months.
- Cetuximab benefit was attenuated in KRAS-mutant, NRAS-mutant, and right-sided-primary subgroups (interactions 0.0246, -0.082, and 0.0212 months; all significant).

Other treatment interactions and refuted hypotheses:
- Bevacizumab showed evidence of larger association in stage_iv disease (0.0006 months, p=0.971) but no statistically supported attenuation by venous_thromboembolism_history (-0.0383 months, p=0.288).
- Pembrolizumab attenuation by autoimmune_disease was not supported (-0.0564 months, p=0.302).
- Regorafenib was adverse as a main effect (0.9416 months, p=<1e-250), while the hypothesized worsening with higher ecog_ps was not significant (-0.0388 months per ECOG point, p=7.71e-5).
- Autoimmune disease itself was not an independent adverse prognostic factor in the adjusted model (-0.0115 months, p=0.555).

Overall conclusion: the strongest patterns were clinically coherent treatment-biomarker relationships: pembrolizumab with MSI-high disease, encorafenib with BRAF V600E, trastuzumab/tucatinib with HER2 amplification, and reduced cetuximab benefit in RAS-mutant or right-sided disease. Baseline inflammatory, nutritional, and metastatic-burden variables also carried independent prognostic information for progression-free survival. Several safety/comorbidity interaction ideas were tested but not statistically supported in this cohort.

